                  <persName id="t17970531-6-person107">
                  THOMAS
                   DALY
               <interp inst="t17970531-6-person107" type="surname" value="DALY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17970531-6-person107" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17970531-6-person107" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am a <rs id="t17970531-6-viclabel23" type="occupation">watchman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17970531-6-victim106 t17970531-6-viclabel23"></join>: I lost the things mentioned in the indictment, on Sunday, the 30th of April, I had them on between one and two o'clock in the afternoon, and between three and four the same day, I found them upon the prisoner, about four or five hundred yards from where I live; she was coming out of a cloaths shop, she had the hat on her head, and the coat and breeches in her apron; I gave her to the constable<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="179705310014"></xptr>with the property; I never saw her before; I believe she was in liquor.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. He gave me the things to hold.</p>
               <p>Daly. No, I did not.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17970531-6-person108">
                  EDWARD
                   SMITH
